    "shortDescription": "Wild hamsters are surprisingly serious engineers — they dig burrows with a sleeping room, a pantry, a bathroom corner, and multiple escape tunnels. Their stretchy cheek pouches can hold so much food that a fully loaded hamster looks almost too round to walk. Fun fact: A Syrian hamster's cheek pouches extend all the way back to its shoulders when completely stuffed."
